	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p><em>People who are trained with simple weapons are also trained in hand-to-hand combat, useful if they don't have access to a weapon.</em></p><p>Your @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-class-features.4km0TjS91nC4PBNL]{Martial Arts} attacks count as &amp;reference[magicweapon], &amp;reference[adamantine], &amp;reference[coldiron], and &amp;reference[silver] for the purpose of overcoming resistance and immunity to nonmagical damage.</p><p>You roll a [[/damage 1d6]] in place of the normal damage dice of your unarmed strike. This die increases to [[/damage 1d8]] at level 5, [[/damage 1d10]] at level 11, and [[/damage 1d12]] at level 17, as shown in the Martial Arts column of the @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-class.VQiQktedzIusKs4y]{monk table}. These increases are also listed later on this page.</p><p>Reference:</p><p>&amp;reference[magic weapon], &amp;Reference[Finesse], &amp;reference[light weapon]</p>",
